10000723: Smooth muscle cells have a single nucleus, and are spindle-shaped. Smooth muscle cells can undergo hyperplasia, mitotically dividing to produce new cells. Ca++ ions trigger contraction when they are released from SR and enter through opened voltage-gated calcium channels.
